functions.label: buildSamplerAggregation
description:
Wraps the supplied aggregations in a sampler aggregation.
A supplied samplerShardSize (the shard_size parameter of the sampler aggregation)
of less than 1 indicates no sampling, and the aggs are returned as-is.

children.label: aggs
description: - The aggregations to be wrapped in the sampler aggregation.

children.label: shardSize
description:
- The shard size parameter for the sampler aggregation.
  A value less than 1 indicates no sampling.

functions.label: fetchAggIntervals
description: Asynchronously fetches aggregation intervals from an Elasticsearch client.

children.label: params
description: - The parameters for fetching aggregation intervals.

returnComment: A promise that resolves to a map of numeric column statistics.

functions.label: fetchHistogramsForFields
description: Asynchronously fetches histograms for specified fields from an Elasticsearch client.

children.label: params
description: The parameters for fetching histograms.

returnComment: A promise that resolves with the fetched histograms.

functions.label: getSamplerAggregationsResponsePath
description:
Returns the path of aggregations in the Elasticsearch response as an array,
depending on whether sampling is being used.

children.label: samplerShardSize
description:
- The shard size parameter of the sampler aggregation.
  A value less than 1 indicates no sampling.

returnComment: An array representing the path of aggregations in the response.

interfaces.label: SignificantItem
description:
Represents significant item metadata for a field/value pair.
This interface is used as a custom type within Log Rate Analysis
for a p-value based variant, not related to the generic
significant terms aggregation type.

children.label: key
description: The key associated with the significant item.

children.label: type
description: The type of the significant item.

children.label: doc_count
description: The document count for the significant item.

children.label: bg_count
description: The background count for the significant item.

children.label: total_doc_count
description: The total document count for all items.

children.label: total_bg_count
description: The total background count for all items.

children.label: score
description: The score associated with the significant item.

children.label: pValue
description: The p-value for the significant item, or null if not available.

children.label: normalizedScore
description: The normalized score for the significant item.

children.label: histogram
description: An optional histogram for the significant item.

children.label: unique
description: Indicates if the significant item is unique within a group.

children.label: logRateChangeSort
description: Calculates a numerical value based on bg_count and doc_count for which to sort log rate change

children.label: pValue

children.label: histogram
description: An optional array of significant item histogram items.

children.label: histogram

children.label: duplicate
